Multi-Converter can use bundled third-party conversion engines. Those engines
are separate third-party software packages and retain their own licenses,
notices, and redistribution conditions.

The Windows x64 V1 application bundles FFmpeg and ffprobe
8.1.1-essentials_build-www.gyan.dev as base sidecar executables, and bundles
advanced engines such as PDFium, LibreOffice, Pandoc, and libvips as app
resources. The FFmpeg build is configured with --enable-gpl, so the bundled
FFmpeg/ffprobe executables are treated as GPL-covered third-party software in
this distribution. Multi-Converter uses these engines as separate local
processes or libraries; the AGPL-3.0-or-later license for Multi-Converter does
not replace their licenses.

Each engine archive must include the applicable license files and, when
required or configured, third-party notices for the engine and its bundled
components. The AGPL-3.0-or-later license for Multi-Converter does not automatically
apply to FFmpeg, ffprobe, PDFium, LibreOffice, Pandoc, libvips, 7-Zip,
or any other third-party engine bundled or distributed for Multi-Converter.

